    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello, when deleting a quickfix error line in buffer and undoing the deletion, the respective quickfix error gets its line incremented, this means that it no longer points to the correct line.\n\n\nSee video for better explanation\n\n<details>\n<summary>video</summary>\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8c4d7a73-1354-4143-a68e-3b49a978e076\n\n</details>\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:grep foo\n:cope\n[Q\ndd\nu\n:cope\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI don't think normal commands should mutate the quickfix at all, even if they should, after undoing the error list points to wrong line\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-3342+g5d85669a33\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, should I report this to vim repo then?\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
